version - september 2022
INFORMATION ON THE PROCESSING OF PERSONAL DATA OF USERS ACCESSING THE WEBSITE
TITOLARE DEL TRATTAMENTO
THE DATA CONTROLLER
of personal data (i.e. the one who decides the reasons why it is necessary to process your personal data and the means to do so) is
AccessiWay S.r.l.
(P.Iva 12419990010) with registered office in Via Pietro Micca n°20, Turin -10122 (TO).You can contact AccessiWay by e-mail by writing to
accessiway@pec.net
.
TYPE OF DATA PROCESSED
For the purpose we will explain in a moment, we need the following data:
navigation data.
WHY WE PROCESS YOUR DATA
PURPOSES OF PROCESSING
We process your personal data for the following purposes:N.B. Compulsory provision means that without the provision of data, the processing of which is necessary to fulfill legal or contractual obligations, it will not be possible to handle your request.The controller processes your personal data in order to fulfill your request for assistance (mandatory provision).
WHAT AUTHORIZES US TO PROCESS YOUR DATA
LEGAL BASIS FOR PROCESSING
The processing is necessary for the performance of a contract to which the data subject is a party or the execution of pre-contractual measures taken at the request of the data subject.
STORAGE OF PERSONAL DATA
The data processed for the above purpose, will be kept from the 'beginning of the work activity and for 10 years from the date of termination of the contract.
RECIPIENTS AND COMMUNICATION OF DATA
The data voluntarily provided using the registration form on the site, will be communicated to the following entities:
companies that perform database management and maintenance services of the Data Controller;
accountant;
external company that will handle payment management;
YOUR RIGHTS
(RIGHTS OF THE DATA SUBJECT)
At any time you can ask us, in the cases provided by law, to:
receive confirmation of the existence of your personal data, access to their content and information related to their processing (right of access);
update, modify and/or correct your personal data (right of rectification);
erase data or restrict their processing if they are processed in violation of the law, including data whose retention is not necessary in relation to the purposes for which the data were collected or otherwise processed (right to be forgotten and right to limitation);
receive copies of data in electronic format about you and request that such data be transmitted to another data controller (right to data portability).
Exercising your rights is free of charge. You may exercise your rights by writing to:
privacy@accessiway.com
We remind you that it is always and in any case YOUR right to complain directly to a supervisory authority and, if you are in Italy, directly to the
Guarantor Authority for the Protection of Personal Data
through the information you will find on the website
www.garanteprivacy.it
(opens in a new tab)
.
